# ========================================
# üìù Usage Examples
# ========================================

# 1. Create .env file
# cp env.example .env

# 2. Edit .env file
# notepad .env (Windows)
# nano .env (Linux/Mac)

# 3. Modify with actual values
# PRIVATE_KEY=0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef

# 4. Verify environment variables
# node -e "require('dotenv').config(); console.log('PRIVATE_KEY:', process.env.PRIVATE_KEY ? 'Set' : 'Not set');"

# ========================================
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  Security Warnings
# ========================================

# - Never commit .env file to Git
# - Ensure .env is included in .gitignore
# - Backup actual private keys in a safe location
# - Use only test accounts, never accounts with real funds
# - Do not share environment variable files

# ========================================
# üöÄ Deployment Commands
# ========================================

# Local Testing
# npm run deploy:localhost

# Testnet Deployment
# npm run deploy:testnet

# Mainnet Deployment
# npm run deploy:mainnet

